# =============================================================================
# THE WEIGHT OF OFFICE: LBJ 1963–1969
# File: lbj_conspiracy.dry
# Purpose: The Seven Days mechanic.
#
# DESIGN NOTES:
#   - coup_conspiracy (lbj_continuity) runs 0-100, hidden from player
#   - Hint cards surface to the player's deck when lbj_continuity crosses thresholds
#   - Each hint is written to be genuinely ambiguous — bureaucratic normality
#     with something slightly wrong in it. DeLillo grammar.
#   - The coup does not "happen" in any normal game. Sub-1% per turn
#     once lbj_continuity > 70. Players who read carefully may piece together
#     what the variables were tracking. Players who don't will simply
#     have felt a low-frequency dread they can't quite name.
#   - If it fires: lbj_ending_coup. An ending unlike the others.
#
# WHAT INCREASES lbj_continuity:
#   - Low credibility (the generals read the papers)
#   - Vietnam de-escalation while military pressure is high
#   - National unity collapse (chaos creates opportunity)
#   - Back-channel diplomacy that cuts around military command
#   - LBJ appearing weak, indecisive, or politically terminal
#   - Certain paranoia-adjacent choices
#
# WHAT DECREASES lbj_continuity:
#   - High approval (legitimacy is the best defense)
#   - High credibility
#   - Keeping the military satisfied on Vietnam
#   - Strength signaling
# =============================================================================

