General LeMay is in excellent spirits at this morning's briefing. He has told a joke — not a good joke, but a joke, which is unusual for him. Afterward he shakes hands with two of the Joint Chiefs with the warmth of men concluding something.

McNamara does not seem to notice. Or he notices and doesn't say so.

The briefing is about logistics. The numbers are fine.

*(You file this away without knowing quite why.)*

- @lbj_main_hand: Continue

