A memo is in your briefing stack that no one has initialed. The routing slip is blank. It concerns contingency planning — a standard enough subject — but the parameters it assumes are not standard. It assumes, without stating it clearly, that certain command authorities might need to be exercised outside normal civilian oversight structures, under extreme circumstances of governmental incapacity.

You read it twice.

You call Jenkins. He comes in, reads it, and shreds it. Neither of you says what you're thinking. This is one of those situations in which saying a thing makes it more real.

You have a 9 a.m. with the Budget Bureau.

*(You go to your 9 a.m.)*

- @lbj_main_hand: Continue

