Russell asks you, almost gently — Russell who has known you since the Senate, who taught you what he knew about power, who has disagreed with you on nearly everything for the past two years — if you have given any thought to your security detail.

You ask him what he means.

He says he's just asking. He's been reading some things. He mentions, briefly, a name you half-recognize — a general, a foreign posting, a year in the early sixties. He drops it.

You tell him your security is fine. He nods in the way of a man who knew you were going to say that and wanted it on the record between you that he asked.

You call the Secret Service director from your car.

The director says everything is fine.

*(Everything is fine.)*

- @lbj_main_hand: Continue

