@lbj_hint_late_call
title: 2 A.M.
is-card: true
card-image: img/phone_card.png
tags: lbj_party_card
view-if: lbj_continuity >= 50 and lbj_continuity_hints < 9
max-visits: 1
on-arrival: lbj_continuity_hints += 1; lbj_paranoia += 8; lbj_continuity -= 5

The phone rings at 2:04 a.m. It is the secure line — not the main line, the secure line that only a specific set of people have the number for.

You pick up.

There is a pause on the other end. Not silence — you can hear the ambient sound of somewhere, an office or a car or something institutional. Then a voice you don't quite recognize says: *"The President should know that certain people are concerned about instability."*

You ask who this is.

The line goes dead.

You lie there in the dark for forty minutes.

In the morning you tell Moyers to find out whose voice that was. He comes back three days later and says he couldn't determine it. His face, when he says this, has something in it he's trying not to show you.

You do not push.

*(The concern about instability, whoever expressed it, is your own concern also. Maybe that's all it was. Someone calling to share a concern.)*

- @lbj_hint_call_action: Take precautions. Talk to someone you trust.
- @lbj_hint_call_ignore: Let it go. You're not going to lose sleep over a crank call.

@lbj_hint_call_action
title: Precautions
on-arrival: lbj_paranoia += 5; lbj_capital -= 4; lbj_continuity -= 8; lbj_approval -= 2

You make some calls of your own. Quiet ones. People who know things without being official about knowing things.

Nobody tells you anything definitive. Several people tell you they've heard nothing unusual, in the specific way that people who have heard something say they've heard nothing.

Your security detail is quietly doubled for two weeks. No announcement. No memo.

Nothing happens. You tell yourself that the nothing that happens is evidence that either you were right to take precautions, or there was nothing to take precautions against. You cannot determine which.

- @lbj_main_hand: Continue

@lbj_hint_call_ignore
title: Crank Call
on-arrival: lbj_continuity += 4

You've been getting crank calls since 1953. You go back to sleep.

In the morning you feel fine. The briefings are normal. McNamara has good charts.

*(You don't tell anyone about the call.)*

- @lbj_main_hand: Continue

